08,315,318,321],{"type":27,"text":54,"spans":55,"direction":24},"This post specifically addresses validator operators participating in the PoS migration. For general information on the migration, see this post: What You Need to Know About Nimiq's Migration to Proof of Stake.",[56,60],{"start":57,"end":58,"type":59},33,52,"strong",{"start":61,"end":62,"type":63,"data":64},145,209,"hyperlink",{"link_type":65,"url":66,"target":67},"Web","https://www.nimiq.com/blog/nimiq-is-migrating-to-proof-of-stake-what-you-need-to-know/","_blank",{"type":27,"text":69,"spans":70,"direction":24},"",[],{"type":27,"text":72,"spans":73,"direction":24},"You can find the full documentation here. Below is a short summary of the next steps for validator operators.",[74],{"start":75,"end":76,"type":63,"data":77},35,40,{"link_type":65,"url":78,"target":67},"https://www.nimiq.com/developers/migration/validator-activation",{"type":80,"text":81,"spans":82,"direction":24},"heading3","Steps for Validator Operators",[83],{"start":41,"end":84,"type":59},29,{"type":27,"text":86,"spans":87,"direction":24},"Main Prerequisite:",[88],{"start":41,"end":89,"type":59},18,{"type":91,"text":92,"spans":93,"direction":24},"list-item","Validator Registration: Your validator needs to be registered and appear on this list.",[94,96],{"start":41,"end":95,"type":59},22,{"start":97,"end":98,"type":63,"data":99},75,85,{"link_type":65,"url":100,"target":67},"https://nimiq.watch/#pre-staking",{"type":27,"text":102,"spans":103,"direction":24},"1. Join the Validator Operator's Chat",[104],{"start":41,"end":105,"type":59},37,{"type":91,"text":107,"spans":108,"direction":24},"Join Nimiq’s Discord or Telegram. Reach out to a Moderator/Team Member to verify yourself as a validator operator.",[109,114],{"start":110,"end":111,"type":63,"data":112},13,20,{"link_type":65,"url":113,"target":67},"https://discord.gg/nimiq",{"start":115,"end":116,"type":63,"data":117},24,32,{"link_type":65,"url":118,"target":67},"https://t.me/nimiq",{"type":27,"text":120,"spans":121,"direction":24},"2. Install the Latest PoW Release, now version 1.6.4, which was released on November 13, 2024.",[122],{"start":41,"end":123,"type":59},94,{"type":91,"text":125,"spans":126,"direction":24},"Download the code here or access compiled binaries here.",[127,131],{"start":128,"end":95,"type":63,"data":129},17,{"link_type":65,"url":130,"target":67},"https://github.com/nimiq/core-js/releases/tag/v1.6.4",{"start":132,"end":133,"type":63,"data":134},50,55,{"link_type":65,"url":135,"target":67},"https://www.nimiq.com/developers/build/nimiq-pow/downloads.html",{"type":91,"text":137,"spans":138,"direction":24},"Syncing Shortcut: Download a snapshot via IPFS or Torrent, extract it, and place it in your PoW client directory to speed up sync time. If using a third-party source, verify it with this SHA256 hash:",[139,141,146],{"start":41,"end":140,"type":59},16,{"start":142,"end":143,"type":63,"data":144},42,46,{"link_type":65,"url":145,"target":67},"https://ipfs.nimiq.io/ipfs/QmRKvFVpTdXagvgZG5cF9qdz13x9DkZhUvwXAS5YMaqTfu?filename=pow-main-full-consensus.zip",{"start":132,"end":147,"type":63,"data":148},57,{"link_type":65,"url":149,"target":67},"https://repo.nimiq.com/torrents/nimiq-pow-main-full-consensus.torrent",{"type":27,"text":69,"spans":151,"direction":24},[],{"type":27,"text":153,"spans":154,"direction":24},"\u003Ccode style=\"font-family: Fira Code; background: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.06);padding: 4px;border-radius: 4px;color: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.8);font-size: 0.8em;\">97fba2d6a9c8eaeb5fe568337e8052097fdffaae3f047b2f283e7007f30851cf  pow-main-full-consensus.zip\u003C/code>",[155],{"start":41,"end":156,"type":157,"data":158},252,"label",{"label":159},"HTML",{"type":27,"text":161,"spans":162,"direction":24},"3. Download the Latest PoS Release, now 1.0.0-rc.5, which was released on November 17, 2024.",[163],{"start":41,"end":164,"type":59},92,{"type":91,"text":166,"spans":167,"direction":24},"Download it here.",[168],{"start":169,"end":140,"type":63,"data":170},8,{"link_type":65,"url":171,"target":67},"https://github.com/nimiq/core-rs-albatross/releases/tag/v1.0.0-rc.5",{"type":27,"text":173,"spans":174,"direction":24},"4. Verify your Configuration",[175],{"start":41,"end":176,"type":59},28,{"type":91,"text":178,"spans":179,"direction":24},"Configure client.toml with your validator data as explained in Step 1 of the Activation Guide. ",[180],{"start":181,"end":182,"type":63,"data":183},63,93,{"link_type":65,"url":184,"target":67},"https://www.nimiq.com/developers/migration/validator-activation#step-1-add-validator-data-into-the-configuration-file",{"type":91,"text":186,"spans":187,"direction":24},"Verify that the seed list matches the list provided in the client.example.toml. The same list is provided below for confirmation:",[188],{"start":189,"end":190,"type":63,"data":191},59,78,{"link_type":65,"url":192,"target":67},"https://github.com/nimiq/core-rs-albatross/blob/albatross/lib/src/config/config_file/client.example.toml#L35C1-L51C2",{"type":27,"text":194,"spans":195,"direction":24},"\u003Cpre style=\"font-family: Fira Code; background: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.06);padding: 12px;border-radius: 4px;color: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.8);font-size: 0.8em;\">seed_nodes = [\n  { address = \"/dns4/aurora.seed.nimiq.com/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/catalyst.seed.nimiq.network/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/cipher.seed.nimiq-network.com/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/eclipse.seed.nimiq.cloud/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/lumina.seed.nimiq.systems/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/nebula.seed.nimiq.com/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/nexus.seed.nimiq.network/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/polaris.seed.nimiq-network.com/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/photon.seed.nimiq.cloud/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/pulsar.seed.nimiq.systems/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/quasar.seed.nimiq.com/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/solstice.seed.nimiq.network/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/vortex.seed.nimiq.cloud/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/zenith.seed.nimiq.systems/tcp/443/wss\" },\n]\u003C/pre>",[196,199,203,207,211,215,219,223,227,231,235,239,243,247,251,255],{"start":41,"end":197,"type":157,"data":198},166,{"label":159},{"start":200,"end":201,"type":157,"data":202},169,225,{"label":159},{"start":204,"end":205,"type":157,"data":206},228,290,{"label":159},{"start":208,"end":209,"type":157,"data":210},293,357,{"label":159},{"start":212,"end":213,"type":157,"data":214},360,419,{"label":159},{"start":216,"end":217,"type":157,"data":218},422,482,{"label":159},{"start":220,"end":221,"type":157,"data":222},485,541,{"label":159},{"start":224,"end":225,"type":157,"data":226},544,603,{"label":159},{"start":228,"end":229,"type":157,"data":230},606,671,{"label":159},{"start":232,"end":233,"type":157,"data":234},674,732,{"label":159},{"start":236,"end":237,"type":157,"data":238},735,795,{"label":159},{"start":240,"end":241,"type":157,"data":242},798,854,{"label":159},{"start":244,"end":245,"type":157,"data":246},857,919,{"label":159},{"start":248,"end":249,"type":157,"data":250},922,980,{"label":159},{"start":252,"end":253,"type":157,"data":254},983,1043,{"label":159},{"start":256,"end":257,"type":157,"data":258},1044,1051,{"label":159},{"type":27,"text":69,"spans":260,"direction":24},[],{"type":91,"text":262,"spans":263,"direction":24},"Verify the network configuration entry is set to main-albatross as provided in the client.example.toml. The final configuration should be the same one as below",[264],{"start":265,"end":266,"type":63,"data":267},83,102,{"link_type":65,"url":268,"target":67},"https://github.com/nimiq/core-rs-albatross/blob/albatross/lib/src/config/config_file/client.example.toml#L121",{"type":27,"text":270,"spans":271,"direction":24},"\u003Ccode style=\"font-family: Fira Code; background: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.06);padding: 4px;border-radius: 4px;color: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.8);font-size: 0.8em;\">network = \"main-albatross\"\u003C/code>",[272],{"start":41,"end":273,"type":157,"data":274},185,{"label":159},{"type":27,"text":69,"spans":276,"direction":24},[],{"type":27,"text":278,"spans":279,"direction":24},"5. Compile the PoS Client",[280],{"start":41,"end":281,"type":59},25,{"type":91,"text":283,"spans":284,"direction":24},"Compile the PoS client as explained in Step 4 of the Activation Guide.",[285],{"start":286,"end":287,"type":63,"data":288},39,69,{"link_type":65,"url":289,"target":67},"https://www.nimiq.com/developers/migration/validator-activation#step-4-run-the-activation-tool",{"type":27,"text":69,"spans":291,"direction":24},[],{"type":27,"text":293,"spans":294,"direction":24},"6. Run the Activation Tool",[295],{"start":41,"end":296,"type":59},26,{"type":91,"text":298,"spans":299,"direction":24},"The activation tool will stay active until the end of the migration. It will signal “online” starting approximately 3 days before the candidate block at Proof of Work block #3’456’000. ",[],{"type":91,"text":301,"spans":302,"direction":24},"Once your validator “online” signal has been sent, it will appear as ONLINE on the Migration Readiness Monitor.",[303],{"start":304,"end":305,"type":63,"data":306},82,110,{"link_type":65,"url":307,"target":67},"https://nimiq-migration-monitor.netlify.app",{"type":91,"text":309,"spans":310,"direction":24},"When the Activation Phase opens and your validator produces a Genesis Hash, it will appear as READY on the Migration Readiness Monitor.",[311],{"start":312,"end":313,"type":63,"data":314},106,134,{"link_type":65,"url":307,"target":67},{"type":91,"text":316,"spans":317,"direction":24},"When more than 80% of the total stake has signaled readiness with the same Genesis Hash, the PoS chain will go live, and validators will begin producing blocks.",[],{"type":27,"text":319,"spans":320,"direction":24},"Remember to start this process as early as possible to ensure a smooth migration to Proof of Stake. Your dedication and support are invaluable in making this transition a success. Thank you for being an essential part of this journey. See you on the Proof of Stake Network!\n",[],{"type":27,"text":322,"spans":323,"direction":24},"Pura Vida\nTeam Nimiq",[324],{"start":41,"end":325,"type":59},9,"grey","rich_text$76ee4a41-ddd5-4810-b3fd-058cea84049e","rich_text",{},{"appsGroupName":331,"appsLinks":332,"howToTitle":454,"howToLinks":455,"appsAdditionalFooterLinks":471,"techGroupName":472,"techLinks":473,"githubLinkLabel":519,"techAdditionalFooterLinks":520,"communityGroupName":521,"communityLinks":522,"communityAdditionalFooterLinks":563,"projectGroupName":564,"projectLinks":565,"projectAdditionalFooterLinks":609,"getStartedGroupName":610,"getStartedLinks":611,"newToCryptoTitle":6,"newToCryptoLinks":629,"getStartedAdditionalFooterLinks":630,"andMoreGroupName":631,"andMoreLinks":632,"legalPages":652,"extraHeaderLinks":653,"newsletterCta":654,"newsletterPlaceholder":655,"socialMediaCta":656,"nimiqShortDescription":657,"hothref":658,"hottext":665,"hotsince":666,"hotuntil":6,"announcementBannerHeadline":667,"announcementBannerCtaLabel":668,"announcementBannerCtaLink":669,"announcementBannerShow":18,"blocks":672,"copyrightNotice":789},"Apps",[333,361,388,408,430],{"logo":334,"visual":343,"label":352,"href":353},{"dimensions":335,"alt":337,"copyright":6,"url":338,"id":339,"edit":340},{"width":336,"height":336},48,"Nimiq Logo","https://nimiq.cdn.prismic.io/nimiq/0dbc2a74-5cfb-4b19-a734-611379f6a591_nimiq-product-icon.svg","YlWuhRIAAC0AZFYp",{"x":41,"y":41,"zoom":341,"background":342},2,"#fff",{"dimensions":344,"alt":347,"copyright":6,"url":348,"id":349,"edit":350},{"width":345,"height":346},594,384,"Screenshot of the Nimiq Wallet","https://images.prismic.io/nimiq/18669675-be09-47fd-99bf-5c6eb8e091c0_header-wallet-hero.jpg?auto=compress,format&rect=0,0,817,528&w=594&h=384","ZPXRPBEAACEAS93s",{"x":41,"y":41,"zoom":351,"background":342},0.7272727272727273,"Wallet",{"id":354,"type":355,"tag